us  .","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, or North German   Magnussen  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Leopard","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic origin, derived from <i>leon</i> ‘lion’ + <i>hard</i> ‘hardy, brave, strong’. This was the name of a 5th-century Frankish saint, the patron of peasants and horses. Although it was introduced into Britain by the Normans, <i>Leonard</i> was an uncommon name during the Middle Ages. It was revived in some areas towards the end of the 1400s, and in the 19th‐century became very popular. It is now also common as a Jewish name (  compare  Leon  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Lennard","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Leonard  , in part a transferred use of the surname, which was derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]},{"name":"Nilsson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Lars, Nils, Per, Anders, Egil, Lennart, Sven, Birgit, Fredrik, Sten, Algot.  German Kurt, Hans, Otto, Gerhard, Gotthard, Karl-Heinz.","Swedish and German: patronymic from the personal name <i>Nils</i>, a shortened form of <i>Nikolaus</i>. Compare   Nilson  ,   Neilson   3, and   Nielson   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Nilson","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which originated in the Middle Ages as either a patronymic from   Neil   or a metronymic from   Nell .  Use as a given name probably began as a tribute to the British admiral  Lord Nelson  (  1758–1805 ), the victor of the Battle of Trafalgar;  see also  Horatio .  It is, however, now much more common in the United States than in Britain, its popularity there in the 1930s and 40s no doubt having been influenced by the American film actor and singer  Nelson Eddy  (  1901–67 ). Nowadays the name is universally associated with the South African statesman  Nelson Mandela  (  b. 1918 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Finvid Leopard Nilsson Magnuson was born in 1285 as the son of Nils. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Kristina Magnusdotter."},"et":{"1285–":"1285–Surnud","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"Surnud","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285"},"fi":{"1285–":"1285–Kuollut","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"Kuollut","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285"},"fr":{"1285–":"1285–Décédé","1285–Male":"1285–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"Décédé","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285","lifeSummary":"Finvid Leopard Nilsson Magnuson est né en 1285, fils de Nils. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Kristina Magnusdotter."},"de":{"1285–":"1285–Verstorben","1285–Male":"1285–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"Verstorben","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285","lifeSummary":"Finvid Leopard Nilsson Magnuson wurde 1285, als Sohn von Nils geboren. Er hatte mit Kristina Magnusdotter mindestens 1 Sohn und 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1285–":"1285–Desede","1285–Male":"1285–Desede","–Female":"Desede","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"Desede","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285"},"hu":{"1285–":"1285–elhunyt","1285–Male":"1285–elhunyt","–Female":"elhunyt","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"elhunyt","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285"},"id":{"1285–":"1285–Telah Meninggal","1285–Male":"1285–TelahMeninggal","–Female":"Telah Meninggal","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":"TelahMeninggal","1346":"1346","1379":"1379","1330":"1330","1285":"1285"},"it":{"1285–":"1285–Deceduto","1285–Male":"1285–Deceduto","–Female":"Deceduta","1330–1379":"1330–1379","–1346":"–1346","–Male":